HARVARD UNDERGRADUATE MATHEMATICS ASSOCIATION

Harvard Undergraduate Mathematics Association (HUMA) is a student organization dedicated to enriching the undergraduate mathematics community at Harvard by organizing mentorship programs, social events, career panels, and other activities.

2023-24 Events

Career Panel

Fri, Sep 29, 3:30-4:30pm @ Fong Auditorium

Featuring five Harvard seniors:

  • Eric Yan has done research in number theory and behavioral economics at Harvard.

  • Dora Woodruff has done math research at multiple REU programs.

  • Cathy Liang has interned in financial restructuring at Houlihan Lokey and APL Group.

  • Leo Fried has interned in trading at Jane Street.

  • Eric Shen has interned as a software engineer at Stripe and Jane Street.

HUMA-ween

Tue, Oct 31, 4:00-6:00pm @ SC Math Lounge

Join us for a fun Halloween-themed social!

Come to chat with professors, grad students, and fellow undergrads with FREE FOOD (including custom cookies from Flour Bakery, candy , and more!). We'll also have a photo booth set up with props and costumes to take spooky photos with your friends!

Everyone is welcome!

Talk Day

Fri, Dec 8, 4:30-6:30pm @ SC 507

We'll have five undergraduate presenters talking about a variety of math-related topics, such as normal distributions, mathematical biology, and more! All talks will be accessible to all undergraduates, and snacks will be provided.

  • Warren Zhu

  • Dora Woodruff

  • Alan Wang

  • Emma Finn

  • Ari Krishna

Game Night

Mon, Dec 11, 7:00-9:00pm @ SC Math Lounge

Game Night is a HUMA tradition! Come take a break from studying for finals and play fun games with free pizza !!

HUMA x GIIM Valentine's Day Social

Wed, Feb 14, 5:30-6:30pm @ SC Math Lounge

HUMA x Tsinghua Mixer

Thu, Feb 15, 4:30-6:30pm @ SC 530, Math Lounge

Join HUMA in welcoming students from Tsinghua University with some cool math talks and a mixer!

Well start off in SC 530 from 4:30-5:15pm with a series of talks from Harvard and Tsinghua students, and then well head over to the Math Lounge from 5:15-6:00pm for the mixer!

Pi Day Celebration

Thu, Mar 21, 7:00-9:00pm @ SC Math Lounge

Join HUMA for a fun and delicious Pi Day celebration, including a Pie Eating Contest and a trivia competition! There will be lots of prizes and pies .

RSVP for the celebration and the Pie Eating Contest (as a participant or spectator) and sign up for the trivia competition (as a team of up to 3 or as an individual).

Visitas Scavenger Hunt

Sun, Apr 14, 5:00-6:00pm @ SC Math Lounge

Bring your friends (in teams of up to 3) or come alone and meet some new friends. Together, you'll solve a series of (loosely) math-related puzzles which take you around the Harvard Science Center. Prizes include speakers, keyboards, and 3blue1brown plushies! Sandwiches from Flour Bakery will be provided.
